[{"Id": 1002291, "EnglishTitle": null, "GujaratiTitle": null, "RUrduTitle": null, "UrduTitle": null, "Sequence": null, "EnglishDescription": "This night is called Laylatul Dahwul Arz. Imam Reza (a) said, “At the 25th night of Ziqadah, Prophet Abraham was born, Prophet Jesus the son of Mary was born, and the earth was spread on the water where the Holy Kaaba is now situated. Hence, if one observes fasting on this day, he will be given the reward of observing fasting in 60 months”. According to another narration, Imam Reza (a) added, “Verily, on this day, Al-Qaaem (Imam Mahdi (a)) will appear.”", "GujaratiDescription": null, "RUrduDescription": "Yeh shab Laylatul Dahwul Arz khelaati hai. Imam Reza (a) farmate hai keh 25th Ziqadah ki shab mein Paighamber Ibrahim (a), Paighamber Isa ibne Maryum ki wiladat huwi thi, aur zameen ko Khana Ka’ba ki taraf se paani par bichaya gaya tha. Neez agar koi is din roza rakkhe to usko 60 mahino ke rozo’n ka sawaab milega. Dusri riwayat se hai keh Imam Reza (a) ne yeh bhi farmaya keh Al-Qaaem (Imam Mahdi (a)) is din zuhoor farmayenge.", "UrduDescription": null, "English": null, "Gujarati": null, "RGujarati": null, "RUrdu": null, "Urdu": null, "RArabic": null, "ArabicText1": null, "ArabicGreenSign1": null, "ArabicRedSign1": null, "ArabicBlueSign1": null, "ArabicText2": null, "ArabicGreenSign2": null, "ArabicRedSign2": null, "ArabicBlueSign2": null, "ArabicText3": null, "ArabicGreenSign3": null, "ArabicRedSign3": null, "ArabicBlueSign3": null, "ArabicText4": null, "ArabicGreenSign4": null, "ArabicRedSign4": null, "ArabicBlueSign4": null, "ArabicText5": null, "ArabicGreenSign5": null, "ArabicRedSign5": null, "ArabicBlueSign5": null, "ArabicText6": null, "ArabicGreenSign6": null, "ArabicRedSign6": null, "ArabicBlueSign6": null, "ArabicText7": null, "ArabicGreenSign7": null, "ArabicRedSign7": null, "ArabicBlueSign7": null, "ArabicText8": null, "ArabicGreenSign8": null, "ArabicRedSign8": null, "ArabicBlueSign8": null, "ArabicText9": null, "A